00:00:02.604 --> 00:00:03.638 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:11.706 --> 00:01:12.540 position:21% line:89% align:start
[singing in Japanese]

00:01:25.452 --> 00:01:28.823 position:19% line:83% align:start
[narrator] The idyllic
island life Nadia had envisioned

00:01:28.856 --> 00:01:31.793 position:30% line:83% align:start
was long since
shown to be a fantasy.

00:01:31.826 --> 00:01:35.697 position:16% line:83% align:start
Typhoon winds tore apart
our heroes' simple home

00:01:35.730 --> 00:01:37.497 position:13% line:89% align:start
and were even strong enough

00:01:37.532 --> 00:01:40.501 position:7% line:83% align:start
to deliver a neighboring island
to their shore,

00:01:40.535 --> 00:01:42.870 position:5% line:89% align:start
truly a marvel of Mother Nature.

00:01:43.838 --> 00:01:45.205 position:24% line:89% align:start
On the new island,

00:01:45.238 --> 00:01:47.474 position:10% line:83% align:start
they discovered their former
friend, Ayerton,

00:01:47.508 --> 00:01:51.679 position:7% line:83% align:start
who warned them that the Kings
of Terror would soon arrive.

00:01:55.750 --> 00:01:57.752 position:41% line:89% align:start
Oh, no.

00:01:57.785 --> 00:02:01.188 position:7% line:89% align:start
It's them, the Kings of Terror!

00:02:01.221 --> 00:02:04.592 position:5% line:83% align:start
A creature of that enormity must
be from the prehistoric era.

00:02:04.626 --> 00:02:06.360 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Wow!
-I don't care where it's from,

00:02:06.393 --> 00:02:08.696 position:21% line:83% align:start
-just what it'll do.
-In July of 1899,

00:02:08.730 --> 00:02:11.431 position:13% line:83% align:start
the world will be destroyed
by the Kings of Terror.

00:02:11.465 --> 00:02:13.568 position:35% line:83% align:start
All living
things will be its prey.

00:02:13.601 --> 00:02:14.669 position:27% line:89% align:start
What do you mean?

00:02:14.702 --> 00:02:16.671 position:16% line:89% align:start
It's an ancient prophecy.

00:02:16.704 --> 00:02:19.741 position:7% line:83% align:start
Yeah, well, that means we still
have ten years left to go.

00:02:19.774 --> 00:02:22.710 position:10% line:83% align:start
Yes, but perhaps they want to
get an early start

00:02:22.744 --> 00:02:24.478 position:10% line:89% align:start
and destroy things gradually.

00:02:24.512 --> 00:02:27.749 position:30% line:83% align:start
-So you mean...
-We're their first victims.

00:02:27.782 --> 00:02:28.816 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Gangway!
-Huh?

00:02:30.317 --> 00:02:31.251 position:44% line:89% align:start
Whoa!

00:02:33.755 --> 00:02:35.823 position:30% line:89% align:start
[all screaming]

00:02:35.857 --> 00:02:37.759 position:38% line:89% align:start
[panting]

00:02:37.792 --> 00:02:40.828 position:19% line:89% align:start
[upbeat music playing]

00:02:43.497 --> 00:02:44.899 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughter]

00:02:44.932 --> 00:02:46.567 position:30% line:83% align:start
-[Marie] Wait!
-Look, Nadia.

00:02:46.601 --> 00:02:48.268 position:7% line:89% align:start
We can run really, really fast.

00:02:48.301 --> 00:02:49.937 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughter]

00:02:51.304 --> 00:02:52.640 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm?

00:02:52.674 --> 00:02:54.374 position:10% line:83% align:start
Not only can you run faster,
you can jump farther.

00:02:54.408 --> 00:02:55.442 position:41% line:89% align:start
Watch!

00:03:00.515 --> 00:03:02.550 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Marie giggling]

00:03:07.254 --> 00:03:10.257 position:27% line:83% align:start
What a mysterious
fantastic island.

00:03:10.290 --> 00:03:12.225 position:35% line:89% align:start
Here we go!

00:03:14.929 --> 00:03:17.865 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughter]

00:03:17.899 --> 00:03:20.935 position:19% line:89% align:start
[upbeat music playing]

00:03:35.482 --> 00:03:36.517 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:03:37.752 --> 00:03:38.986 position:44% line:89% align:start
Whoa!

00:03:39.987 --> 00:03:41.455 position:44% line:89% align:start
Whoa!

00:03:41.488 --> 00:03:43.991 position:19% line:89% align:start
How do we stop it now?

00:03:44.025 --> 00:03:46.661 position:10% line:89% align:start
I'll take care of everything!

00:03:46.694 --> 00:03:49.597 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Witch] Well, did you find
yourself some servants?

00:03:50.765 --> 00:03:53.801 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Ayerton] Oh, shut up and kill
me if that's what you want.

00:03:53.835 --> 00:03:57.471 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Witch] If you're so smart,
how come you ran away from me

00:03:57.505 --> 00:03:59.874 position:16% line:83% align:start
and came all the way back
around from behind?

00:03:59.907 --> 00:04:03.678 position:5% line:83% align:start
My private fleet will anchor off
of these shores any day now.

00:04:03.711 --> 00:04:05.680 position:21% line:83% align:start
When it does, you're
going to be sorry you met me.

00:04:05.713 --> 00:04:08.415 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Witch] I'm so
tired of your arrogance.

00:04:08.448 --> 00:04:10.051 position:30% line:89% align:start
Bow before me!

00:04:10.084 --> 00:04:11.719 position:21% line:83% align:start
All right. All right.
All right. All right.

00:04:11.753 --> 00:04:13.420 position:21% line:89% align:start
I understand you see.

00:04:13.453 --> 00:04:15.556 position:33% line:83% align:start
Surely we can
work out a deal, can't we?

00:04:15.590 --> 00:04:17.592 position:19% line:89% align:start
[Witch] No more deals!

00:04:17.625 --> 00:04:18.993 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:04:19.026 --> 00:04:21.394 position:30% line:83% align:start
Please, please.
Hey, listen to me.

00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:23.497 position:13% line:89% align:start
I have an offering for you.

00:04:23.531 --> 00:04:24.599 position:30% line:89% align:start
Do you want it?

00:04:26.768 --> 00:04:29.003 position:21% line:89% align:start
[overlapping chatter]

00:04:29.036 --> 00:04:29.871 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:04:32.774 --> 00:04:34.575 position:38% line:89% align:start
[screams]

00:04:34.609 --> 00:04:35.910 position:35% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:04:37.779 --> 00:04:39.412 position:30% line:89% align:start
[all groaning]

00:04:40.915 --> 00:04:43.483 position:16% line:89% align:start
At least that stopped us.

00:04:43.518 --> 00:04:44.351 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:04:46.486 --> 00:04:49.624 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Witch] Regardless
of your petty little problems...

00:04:49.657 --> 00:04:52.593 position:7% line:83% align:start
[Grandis Gang] The Grandis Gang
is back in action.

00:04:53.928 --> 00:04:54.996 position:38% line:89% align:start
Grandis?

00:04:55.029 --> 00:04:56.363 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:04:56.396 --> 00:04:57.464 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Who's there?

00:04:57.497 --> 00:04:59.901 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Huh? Oh.
-Is that really you, Nadia?

00:04:59.934 --> 00:05:02.770 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Jean!
-Marie and King.

00:05:02.804 --> 00:05:04.605 position:24% line:89% align:start
[all] You're alive!

00:05:04.639 --> 00:05:06.507 position:35% line:89% align:start
[laughter]

00:05:06.541 --> 00:05:09.376 position:21% line:89% align:start
[slow music playing]

00:05:11.512 --> 00:05:14.949 position:33% line:83% align:start
I heard you.
The Nautilus was sunk, was it?

00:05:15.917 --> 00:05:17.552 position:10% line:89% align:start
Yes, and it was Captain Nemo

00:05:17.585 --> 00:05:20.054 position:5% line:83% align:start
who helped us all four escape in
the nick of time.

00:05:20.087 --> 00:05:22.924 position:21% line:83% align:start
I cannot believe that
powerful ship was bested.

00:05:22.957 --> 00:05:24.391 position:16% line:89% align:start
I really hate to admit it

00:05:24.424 --> 00:05:26.027 position:13% line:83% align:start
but Gargoyle's giant flying
battleship

00:05:26.060 --> 00:05:27.795 position:5% line:89% align:start
was the strongest one after all.

00:05:27.829 --> 00:05:29.797 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Grandis] So my dear Nemo was...

00:05:29.831 --> 00:05:31.899 position:27% line:89% align:start
And Ms. Electra.

00:05:31.933 --> 00:05:34.001 position:27% line:83% align:start
Tragic. All those
brave seamen are dead.

00:05:37.404 --> 00:05:38.539 position:33% line:89% align:start
[King purrs]

00:05:39.707 --> 00:05:40.908 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:05:40.942 --> 00:05:43.343 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Grandis] Sweet, Captain.

00:05:49.050 --> 00:05:50.818 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Marie] What a giant boat.

00:05:50.852 --> 00:05:52.053 position:19% line:89% align:start
You can say that again.

00:05:52.086 --> 00:05:53.453 position:38% line:89% align:start
Sure can.

00:05:53.486 --> 00:05:54.755 position:30% line:89% align:start
I have no idea

00:05:54.789 --> 00:05:56.991 position:7% line:83% align:start
that a submersible of this size
even existed.

00:05:57.024 --> 00:05:58.659 position:13% line:89% align:start
It's beyond modern science.

00:05:58.693 --> 00:06:00.460 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sneezes]

00:06:00.493 --> 00:06:02.429 position:33% line:83% align:start
No one taught
them their manners.

00:06:02.462 --> 00:06:04.431 position:16% line:89% align:start
Welcome aboard our ship.

00:06:04.464 --> 00:06:05.967 position:16% line:89% align:start
Make yourselves at home.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.035 position:13% line:83% align:start
You do not have to identify
yourself

00:06:08.069 --> 00:06:09.804 position:13% line:89% align:start
to someone wearing a mask.

00:06:09.837 --> 00:06:13.507 position:19% line:83% align:start
Right. I am 1st Officer
and lecturer at your service.

00:06:13.541 --> 00:06:14.675 position:19% line:89% align:start
Pardon us, good woman.

00:06:14.709 --> 00:06:15.943 position:38% line:89% align:start
I might.

00:06:15.977 --> 00:06:17.645 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Who are you?
-Huh?

00:06:17.678 --> 00:06:19.981 position:24% line:83% align:start
I am the captain of
this mighty submarine.

00:06:20.014 --> 00:06:21.949 position:16% line:89% align:start
And you may call me Nemo.

00:06:21.983 --> 00:06:23.985 position:35% line:83% align:start
One moment,
tell me your name again.

00:06:25.553 --> 00:06:26.687 position:44% line:89% align:start
Nemo.

00:06:26.721 --> 00:06:28.923 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Good day.
-Nemo, Captain Nemo.

00:06:28.956 --> 00:06:30.124 position:41% line:89% align:start
Uh-huh.

00:06:31.659 --> 00:06:35.129 position:30% line:83% align:start
[sighs] I shall
never see him again.

00:06:35.162 --> 00:06:36.831 position:21% line:83% align:start
-[Jean] Don't worry.
-Huh?

00:06:36.864 --> 00:06:39.033 position:30% line:83% align:start
I wouldn't jump
to such conclusions.

00:06:39.066 --> 00:06:41.068 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'm sure they're all alive
and well somewhere.

00:06:41.102 --> 00:06:43.170 position:7% line:83% align:start
Well, Jean, you certainly have
grown up

00:06:43.204 --> 00:06:44.872 position:16% line:89% align:start
to be a strong young man.

00:06:44.906 --> 00:06:46.707 position:33% line:89% align:start
Right? Right?

00:06:46.741 --> 00:06:48.142 position:33% line:89% align:start
I don't know.

00:06:48.175 --> 00:06:50.511 position:16% line:83% align:start
Oh, you don't have an eye
for men yet, young lady.

00:06:50.544 --> 00:06:53.080 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'm sure glad
three of you are safe.

00:06:53.114 --> 00:06:55.516 position:27% line:83% align:start
We owe it all to
my brave Gratan.

00:06:55.549 --> 00:06:57.518 position:24% line:83% align:start
So how did you all
end up on this island?

00:06:57.551 --> 00:06:59.687 position:21% line:89% align:start
Thank you for asking.

00:06:59.720 --> 00:07:02.023 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's an epic tale fraught with
danger, suspense,

00:07:02.056 --> 00:07:03.691 position:16% line:89% align:start
and redheaded derring-do.

00:07:03.724 --> 00:07:06.160 position:10% line:83% align:start
We set out from the Nautilus
to launch our counterattack

00:07:06.193 --> 00:07:08.729 position:7% line:83% align:start
against the flying battleship,
but we got caught.

00:07:08.763 --> 00:07:10.531 position:13% line:89% align:start
The crossfire was horrible.

00:07:10.564 --> 00:07:11.666 position:35% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:07:13.801 --> 00:07:15.836 position:10% line:83% align:start
[Nadia] I remember that, you
fled before the battle was over.

00:07:15.870 --> 00:07:17.138 position:24% line:89% align:start
[Hanson] Not true.

00:07:17.171 --> 00:07:18.471 position:21% line:89% align:start
We had a brief chance

00:07:18.506 --> 00:07:20.574 position:16% line:83% align:start
to actually put our plan
into effect.

00:07:20.608 --> 00:07:22.710 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Sanson] In the end,
it was up to me to deliver

00:07:22.743 --> 00:07:24.645 position:13% line:89% align:start
that flying behemoth a blow

00:07:24.679 --> 00:07:26.847 position:19% line:83% align:start
it would jolly well not
soon forget.

00:07:26.881 --> 00:07:29.750 position:35% line:89% align:start
[explosion]

00:07:29.784 --> 00:07:32.253 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Grandis] Everything
was fine up to that point.

00:07:32.286 --> 00:07:33.821 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Hanson] Then the enemy
submarines

00:07:33.854 --> 00:07:35.156 position:30% line:83% align:start
blew a hole in
our balloon,

00:07:35.189 --> 00:07:38.192 position:24% line:83% align:start
and we spiraled off
not knowing where we would land.

00:07:38.225 --> 00:07:39.927 position:10% line:89% align:start
[Grandis] After several days,

00:07:39.961 --> 00:07:43.030 position:10% line:83% align:start
we drifted ashore and landed
on this charming little island.

00:07:43.064 --> 00:07:45.032 position:7% line:89% align:start
But our troubles weren't over.

00:07:45.066 --> 00:07:48.169 position:13% line:83% align:start
We found that this dummy of
a count was already living here.

00:07:48.202 --> 00:07:49.236 position:44% line:89% align:start
What?

00:07:49.270 --> 00:07:50.905 position:10% line:89% align:start
Did you just call me a dummy?

00:07:50.938 --> 00:07:53.107 position:10% line:83% align:start
You better never ever call me
that again,

00:07:53.140 --> 00:07:54.875 position:30% line:83% align:start
you scoundrel,
do you understand?

00:07:54.909 --> 00:07:57.244 position:5% line:83% align:start
Listen, dummy, if I want to call
you a dummy

00:07:57.278 --> 00:07:58.946 position:27% line:83% align:start
then you will be
called a dummy!

00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:00.247 position:19% line:83% align:start
Do you understand that,
you dummy!

00:08:00.281 --> 00:08:01.949 position:27% line:89% align:start
Of all the cheek!

00:08:01.983 --> 00:08:04.618 position:13% line:83% align:start
I just told you not to call
me that, you hear me, do you?

00:08:04.652 --> 00:08:07.121 position:30% line:83% align:start
Somehow I just
can't seem to stop myself.

00:08:07.154 --> 00:08:09.657 position:13% line:83% align:start
Dummy, dummy, dummy, dummy,
dummy, dummy, dummy, dummy.

00:08:09.690 --> 00:08:10.490 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Ayerton] Stop that.
Stop that right now.

00:08:10.524 --> 00:08:11.726 position:38% line:83% align:start
[Sanson]
Dummy, dummy, dummy, dummy.

00:08:11.759 --> 00:08:12.960 position:10% line:89% align:start
Did you say something, dummy?

00:08:12.994 --> 00:08:14.295 position:19% line:83% align:start
-What was that, dummy?
-[Ayerton] Nothing.

00:08:14.328 --> 00:08:15.997 position:10% line:83% align:start
-[Sanson] Nothing, eh? Dummy.
-[chuckles]

00:08:16.030 --> 00:08:17.865 position:10% line:83% align:start
So you are the dreaded witch
all along, right, Ms. Grandis?

00:08:17.898 --> 00:08:19.867 position:27% line:89% align:start
What? What witch?

00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:21.802 position:35% line:83% align:start
That's what
the man with the beard said.

00:08:21.836 --> 00:08:23.637 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[King purrs]
-He's a liar.

00:08:23.671 --> 00:08:25.239 position:10% line:89% align:start
Never believe a word he says

00:08:25.272 --> 00:08:27.274 position:19% line:83% align:start
and be sure not to turn
your back on him.

00:08:27.308 --> 00:08:29.076 position:38% line:83% align:start
-A liar.
-[King purrs]

00:08:29.110 --> 00:08:32.747 position:21% line:83% align:start
He lorded over us and
then stole our food and liquor

00:08:32.780 --> 00:08:35.116 position:24% line:83% align:start
and left us nothing
of our own to live on.

00:08:35.149 --> 00:08:37.551 position:19% line:89% align:start
We put a stop to that.

00:08:37.585 --> 00:08:39.687 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Nadia] So that's why
he was buried in the sand.

00:08:39.720 --> 00:08:41.655 position:13% line:83% align:start
I knew there was something
suspicious about him.

00:08:41.689 --> 00:08:43.257 position:21% line:89% align:start
I never trusted him.

00:08:43.290 --> 00:08:45.659 position:7% line:83% align:start
So, Hanson, the Gratan has been
grounded

00:08:45.693 --> 00:08:47.661 position:19% line:83% align:start
because the balloon has
been hauled?

00:08:47.695 --> 00:08:50.664 position:10% line:83% align:start
Otherwise, we'd have been off
this island a long time ago.

00:08:50.698 --> 00:08:53.267 position:13% line:83% align:start
Why don't you simply repair
the canvas then?

00:08:53.300 --> 00:08:54.769 position:27% line:89% align:start
Excellent point.

00:08:54.802 --> 00:08:56.937 position:19% line:83% align:start
We finally have enough
people to do it now.

00:08:56.971 --> 00:09:00.641 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's been far too long since
I've had a project to work on.

00:09:00.674 --> 00:09:03.811 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well now, you sound sentimental.

00:09:03.844 --> 00:09:06.047 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's nothing to do
on a deserted island.

00:09:06.080 --> 00:09:08.149 position:30% line:83% align:start
[Hanson] Well,
this island is also deserted.

00:09:08.182 --> 00:09:09.917 position:35% line:89% align:start
Then again,

00:09:09.950 --> 00:09:11.685 position:10% line:83% align:start
science is the art of making
something out of nothing.

00:09:11.719 --> 00:09:13.020 position:21% line:89% align:start
[Jean] That's right.

00:09:13.054 --> 00:09:16.991 position:24% line:83% align:start
Um, but this is no
ordinary desert island.

00:09:17.024 --> 00:09:19.960 position:33% line:83% align:start
-[both] Huh?
-[Grandis] Hanson's correct.

00:09:19.994 --> 00:09:21.962 position:33% line:83% align:start
There are no
other living creatures,

00:09:21.996 --> 00:09:24.865 position:13% line:83% align:start
but we sense that something
is very much alive here.

00:09:24.899 --> 00:09:27.868 position:24% line:83% align:start
Mr. Ayerton told us
that this is a peculiar island.

00:09:27.902 --> 00:09:30.037 position:13% line:83% align:start
So I guess that means he's
not a complete liar.

00:09:30.071 --> 00:09:32.940 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right!

00:09:32.973 --> 00:09:34.975 position:7% line:89% align:start
I am not a liar, or a butcher,

00:09:35.009 --> 00:09:37.211 position:16% line:83% align:start
or what you savagely call
a dummy.

00:09:37.244 --> 00:09:40.147 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, then what exactly are you?

00:09:40.181 --> 00:09:44.151 position:10% line:83% align:start
I, my ignorant friend and the
one and only true Count Ayerton,

00:09:44.185 --> 00:09:46.087 position:7% line:89% align:start
and now, I shall make my leave.

